description: Two-input recombinase logic AND gate. Produces GFP only when two recombinases have been expressed and acted on the DNA registers (binary output number: 0001). Consists of a promoter followed by two transcriptors (asymmetric transcriptional terminators flanked by inverted recombination sites) in blocking orientation placed in series. When both terminators are inverted, GFP is expressed. Operated by recombinases Bxb1 and TP901 (e.g. using the dual controller). Low copy ppSC101 ori (5-10 copies)- Ampicilin resistance.
citations: Amplifying genetic logic gates. Bonnet J, Yin P, Ortiz ME, Subsoontorn P, Endy D. Science. 2013 May 3;340(6132):599-603. doi: 10.1126/science.1232758. Epub 2013 Mar 28. 10.1126/science.1232758 PubMed 23539178

description: Two-input recombinase logic OR gate. Produces GFP when one or two recombinases have been expressed and acted on the DNA registers (binary output number: 0111). Consists of a promoter followed by one transcriptional terminator flanked by nested parallel recombination sites. Recombination excises the terminator and allows for the expression of downstream GFP. Operated by recombinases Bxb1 and TP901 (e.g. using the dual controller). Low copy pSC101 ori (5-10 copies)- Ampicilin resistance.
citations: Amplifying genetic logic gates. Bonnet J, Yin P, Ortiz ME, Subsoontorn P, Endy D. Science. 2013 May 3;340(6132):599-603. doi: 10.1126/science.1232758. Epub 2013 Mar 28. 10.1126/science.1232758 PubMed 23539178

description: Two-input recombinase logic NOR gate. Produces GFP only when no recombinase has been expressed and acted on the DNA registers (binary output number: 1000). Consists of a promoter followed by two transcriptors (asymmetric transcriptional terminators flanked by inverted recombination sites) in permissive orientation placed in series. When one or both terminators are inverted, GFP is not expressed anymore. Operated by recombinases Bxb1 and TP901 (e.g. using the dual controller). Low copy ppSC101 ori (5-10 copies)- Ampicilin resistance.
citations: Amplifying genetic logic gates. Bonnet J, Yin P, Ortiz ME, Subsoontorn P, Endy D. Science. 2013 May 3;340(6132):599-603. doi: 10.1126/science.1232758. Epub 2013 Mar 28. 10.1126/science.1232758 PubMed 23539178

description: Two-input recombinase logic XOR gate. Produces GFP when only one of two recombinases have been expressed and acted on the DNA registers (binary output number: 0110). Consists of a promoter followed by one transcriptional terminator flanked by nested recombination sites in an inverted orientation. The action of either recombinase inverts the terminator and allows for the expression of downstream GFP. The action of the second recombinase put the terminator back in blocking orientation. Operated by recombinases Bxb1 and TP901 (e.g. using the dual controller). Low copy pSC101 ori (5-10 copies)- Ampicilin resistance.
citations: Amplifying genetic logic gates. Bonnet J, Yin P, Ortiz ME, Subsoontorn P, Endy D. Science. 2013 May 3;340(6132):599-603. doi: 10.1126/science.1232758. Epub 2013 Mar 28. 10.1126/science.1232758 PubMed 23539178

description: Contains pTET-Bxb1 integrase inducible by anhydrotetracyclin (AtC) and pBAD-TP901 integrase inducible by arabinose. Can be used to control two-input logic gates. Regulated ColE1 ori (50-75 copies); Chloramphenicol resistance.
